# DaisyUI Theming Guidelines

## Theme Configuration
The project's theme configuration is managed through [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts). DaisyUI provides built-in themes and supports custom themes.

## Available Themes
DaisyUI themes are enabled globally. Common themes include:
- `light` - Default light theme
- `dark` - Default dark theme
- `cupcake` - Light pastel theme
- `cyberpunk` - High contrast theme
- `forest` - Dark green theme
- And many more...

## Theme Usage
To apply themes:
1. Use the `data-theme` attribute on HTML elements
2. Apply themes at the root level for global changes
3. Apply themes to specific containers for component-level theming

Example:
```html
<div data-theme="dark">
  <!-- Dark themed content -->
</div>
```

## Color System
DaisyUI provides semantic color classes:
- `primary` - Primary brand color
- `secondary` - Secondary brand color
- `accent` - Accent color
- `neutral` - Neutral color
- `info` - Information color
- `success` - Success color
- `warning` - Warning color
- `error` - Error color

Use these in combination with component classes:
- `btn-primary`
- `bg-primary`
- `text-primary`
- `border-primary`
